main event: A bright, bluish-white object was observed in the sky near the coordinates 19.31N 171.43E in the Far East on May 30, 1964.
interesting points: The object was much larger than a first magnitude star.
The object appeared to be in flight, moving on a northeast course.
The object disappeared behind trees at an elevation of 62 to 70 degrees above the horizon.
The object was observed to be moving extremely fast.
The report indicates that the most probable explanation was a meteor.
